#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import/Exporting"
msgstr "Uvoz/Izvoz"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you attend a family party, a company meeting, a conference, or any other "
"event where other &kphotoalbum; users may be present, you may wish to share "
"your images with those people. You may of course choose to generate &HTML; "
"pages for them to browse, but given you already have spent time classifying "
"all images (Who is on the images, where were they taken etc), there are no "
"reason for them to redo all that work."
msgstr ""
"Ako prisustvuje porodičnoj zabavi, sastanku u firmi, konferenciji ili bilo "
"kojem drugom događaju, gdje drugi &kphotoalbum; korisnici mogu biti "
"prisutni, možda želite podijeliti svoje slike sa tim ljudima. Vi, naravno, "
"možete izabrati za generiranje &HTML; stranice koje biste pretraživali, ali "
"s obzirom na već provedeno vrijeme klasifikacije svih slika (Ko je na "
"slikama, gdje su bile uzete itd), nema razloga da se ponovi sav posao."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kphotoalbum; allows you to export a set of your images into a <literal role="
"\"extension\">.kim</literal> file, which other people may import into their "
"database, to get your classification for these images."
msgstr ""
"&kphotoalbum; vam omogućava izvozete set slika u <literal role=\"extension"
"\">. Kim </literal>datoteka, koju su ostali ljudi mogli uvesti u svoje baze "
"podataka, da biste dobili vašu klasifikaciju za ove slike."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two different kind of <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files "
"exists, inlines or externals, referring to whether the images them self are "
"located in the file or at some other location. Placing the images in the "
"file has the obvious advantage that the file is self contained, while it has "
"the equally obvious disadvantage of the file being rather big."
msgstr ""
"Dvije različite vrste <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal>postijećih "
"datoteka, unutarnjih ili vanjskih, pozivajući se da li se njihove slike samo "
"nalaze u datoteci ili na nekoj drugoj lokaciji. Postavljanje slika u "
"datoteci ima očiglednu prednost za samostalnu datoteku, dok ima jednako "
"očiglednu manu jer je datoteka prilično velika."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two places from which you may generate a <literal role=\"extension"
"\">.kim</literal> file, namely directly from <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Export...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, or along with "
"&HTML; pages (see <xref linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>). Creating a "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file during &HTML; export will "
"create an external <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file."
msgstr ""
"Postoje dva mjesta iz kojih možete generirati <literal role=\"extension\">. "
"kim </literal>datoteka, i to uglavnom direktno iz "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Export ... </"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, ili zajedno sa &HTML; stranice (pogledaj <xref "
"linkend=\"chp-generating-html\"/>). Stvaranje <literal role=\"extension\">."
"kim</literal>datoteka  &HTML.; izvoz će stvoriti eksternu <literal role="
"\"extension\">. kim </literal>datoteku."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"External <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files will search for "
"images in one of two ways. First it will try to look for the images next to "
"the <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file, and if not found, it "
"will search for them at the URL specified when the <literal role=\"extension"
"\">.kim</literal> file was created. Notice the later is only possible for "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files created during &HTML; "
"export."
msgstr ""
"Vanjske <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteke će tražiti slike "
"na jedan od dva načina. Prvo će pokušati tražiti slike pored <literal role="
"\"extension\">.kim</literal>datoteke, a ako nije pronađena, on će ih tražiti "
"na navedenom URL kada je <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteka "
"stvorena. Obratite pažnju da je kasnije jedino moguće za <literal role="
"\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteka stvorenih tokom  &HTML.; izvoza."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export Dialog"
msgstr "Dijalog Izvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section will tell you about the export dialog which you get to from "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Export...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj odjeljak će vam reći o dijalogu izvoza koji će vam doći od "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export ...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most important part of this dialog is specifying whether the <literal "
"role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file should be internal or external (see "
"description above). You have the following three options:"
msgstr ""
"Najvažniji dio ovog dijaloga je navođenja da li <literal role=\"extension\">."
"kim</literal> datoteka trebala biti interna ili vanjska (pogledaj opis "
"gore). Imate sljedeće tri opcije:"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Include in <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file - this will be an "
"internal file"
msgstr ""
"Uključi u <literal role=\"extension\">.kim </literal> datoteka -. Ovo će "
"biti interna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Manual copy next to .kim file - Here you must copy the images yourself next "
"to the .kim file"
msgstr ""
"Ručnu kopiju pored .kim datoteke - Ovdje morate sami kopirati slike pored ."
"kim datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatically copy next to .kim file - here &kphotoalbum; will copy the "
"images for you."
msgstr ""
"Automatski kopirati uz .kim datoteke - ovdje &kphotoalbum; će kopirati slike "
"za vas."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Between you and me, <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> files are "
"really just zip files. Normally it is not worth bothering compressing the "
"files because images normally are compressed JPEG already, and the XML file "
"itself are really tiny. If you really want to squish out the last few bytes, "
"you may still do so, by checking <guilabel>Compress Export File</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"Između tebe i mene, <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteke su "
"zapravo samo zip datoteke. Obično to nije vredno truda sažimanja datoteka, "
"jer obično su slike kompresovane od JPEG već i same XML datoteke su stvarno "
"sitne. Ako stvarno želite da iscijedite  posljednjih nekoliko bajtova, i "
"dalje to možete učiniti, provjerom <guilabel>Kompresor Datoteke za Izvoz</"
"guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The final option on the page are <guilabel>Limit maximum image dimension</"
"guilabel>. When sending some images to some friends, you may not want to "
"send images in full size, as the <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> "
"file might be huge. For this, you may specify that the maximum dimension of "
"images should be say maximum 800 pixels in each direction."
msgstr ""
"Zadnju opciju na stranici je <guilabel>Ograničite maksimalnu dimenziju "
"slike</guilabel>. Prilikom slanja nekih slika prijateljima, možda ne želite "
"da pošaljete slike u punoj veličini, kao <literal role =\"extension\">. kim</"
"literal> datoteka može biti ogromna. Za ovo, možete odrediti da je "
"maksimalna dimenzija slike maksimalno 800 piksela u svakom pravcu."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import Dialog"
msgstr "Dijalog Uvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select a <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> file from a web "
"browser, or choose <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import..."
"</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, &kphotoalbum; will import the database exported "
"with the functionality described in <xref linkend=\"chp-importExport\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Kada odaberete <literal role=\"extension\">.kim</literal> datoteku iz web "
"pretraživača, ili izaberete <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvezi...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, &kphotoalbum; će "
"uvesti iz baze podataka izvezene sa funkcionalnošću opisanom u <xref linkend="
"\"chp-importExport\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The import wizard consist of four steps. First you must specify which images "
"you want to import. Next you must specify in which directory to put the "
"imported images."
msgstr ""
"Čarobnjak za uvoz se sastoji od četiri koraka. Prvo morate odrediti koje "
"slike želite uvesti. Zatim morate odrediti u koji direktorij staviti uvezene "
"slike."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Chances are that you call the people category <emphasis>personen</emphasis> "
"(if you are German), while I in Danish might call this category "
"<emphasis>personer</emphasis>. In the third step of the import dialog, you "
"must specify which category from the import file to import, plus which "
"categories in your database they match."
msgstr ""
"Šanse su da nazovete kategoriju ljudi <emphasis>personen</emphasis> (ako ste "
"Nijemac), dok ja na danskom mogu nazvati ovu kategoriju <emphasis>personer</"
"emphasis>. U trećem koraku dijaloga uvoza, morate navesti koju kategoriju iz "
"uvozne datoteke uvozite, plus koje kategorije u bazi podataka se podudaraju."

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I might call myself in my databases for <emphasis>me</emphasis>, while in "
"your database I'm called Jesper K. Pedersen. Step four let you set up "
"matching for each of the imported categories. This can be see in <xref "
"linkend=\"fig-import-dialog\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Mogu sebe nazvati u svojoj bazi podataka kao <emphasis>ja</emphasis>, dok se "
"u tvojoj bazi podataka zovem Jesper K. Pedersen. Četvrti korak vam dopušta "
"da postavite poklapanje za svaku od kategorija uvoza. To se može vidjeti u "
"<xref linkend =\"fig-import-dijalog\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: importexport.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching People in the Import Dialog"
msgstr "Poklapanje Ljudi u Dijalogu Uvoza"

#. Tag: para
#: importexport.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the screen shot you may see that Donna is the same in both the .kim file "
"and in my database - the name is shown in black to indicate a perfect match "
"in the database. The other three names was not found in the database, though "
"both Jesper and Anne Helene was found matching as substring, so these are "
"suggested. Finally in my database I didn't have Spiff (or I might have named "
"it quite differently), so &kphotoalbum; simply suggest Spiff for the import "
"name."
msgstr ""
"U prikazu ekrana možete vidjeti da je Donna ista u oba .kim datoteci i u "
"mojoj bazi podataka - naziv je prikazan crnim da ukaže na savršeno "
"poklapanje u bazi podataka. Ostala tri imena nisu pronađena u bazi podataka, "
"iako su oboje Jesper i Anne Helene nađene kao podniz, tako da su ovi "
"predloženii. Konačno u mojoj bazi podataka nisam imao Spiff (ili sam ga "
"možda nazvao sasvim drugačije), pa  &kphotoalbum; jednostavno ukazuje Spiff "
"za ime uvoza."
